---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Mission"
  description="Why Badger Journals exists — helping undergraduates read, discuss, and communicate scientific research."
  path="/mission"
>
  <section class="border-b border-border bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.14em] text-primary uppercase">Mission</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-[clamp(2.4rem,5vw,3.6rem)] leading-[1.05] font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance">
        Making scientific research accessible to everyone.
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="mx-auto max-w-[68ch] px-6 py-16 text-lg leading-relaxed text-foreground/80 text-pretty [&>p+p]:mt-6">
    <p>
      As an undergraduate researcher, you are often thrown into the world of research
      with little understanding of how it works. Fortunately, an incredible amount of
      knowledge is freely available online through academic journals and scientific
      publications. However, finding, reading, and understanding primary research
      articles can be challenging, especially for students who are new to research.
    </p>
    <p>
      Equally important, and often even more difficult, is communicating what you learn
      to others. The ability to critically analyze scientific literature, identify key
      findings, and clearly explain complex concepts is essential for success in
      research. Whether you plan to continue in research, attend graduate school, pursue
      medicine, or enter industry, these skills will remain valuable throughout your
      career.
    </p>
    <p>
      Badger Journals was created to help undergraduate students develop these abilities.
      Through reading, discussing, and writing about scientific research, members gain
      experience interpreting scientific literature while staying informed about the
      latest discoveries across a range of fields. Our goal is to make cutting-edge
      research more accessible while helping students become stronger scientists and
      communicators.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
